body:
OK, I'm sorry, I give up on debugging the testWrite issues - I've spent a few hours and I've narrowed it down only to the fact that the client created by WriteFn is spuriously being disconnected, and the broker is being shut down. I wasn't able to even figure out which of these events happens first, too much asynchronous stuff going on. And it happens in different ways (getting different exceptions). But it happens reliably.

Some instructions for reproducing:
- In MqttIOTest, wrap the body of testWrite() into `for (int j = 0; j < 1000; j++)` to get faster test iterations without restarting the whole broker
- To add more logging, do this at the beginning of the test:

```
    java.util.logging.Logger logger = java.util.logging.Logger.getLogger("org.eclipse.paho.client.mqttv3");
// Also tried:
//    java.util.logging.Logger logger = java.util.logging.Logger.getLogger("org.apache.activemq.transport");
    ConsoleHandler handler = new ConsoleHandler();
    handler.setLevel(Level.FINE);
    logger.addHandler(handler);
    logger.setLevel(Level.ALL);
```

I don't know what's going on, but the PR can't go in until this is resolved - at this level of flakiness, it will both destabilize tests and probably just won't work in production either. Hope my debugging instructions help :-/
